@startuml
title Activity Diagram 1 - Full Order Lifecycle

|Customer|
start
:Booking a reservation;

|Waiter|
:Check available table;
if (Reservation exists?) then (yes)
  :Confirm reservation;
else (no)
  :Assign free table;
endif

|System|
:Set table status to OCCUPIED;

|Waiter|
:Take order with menu items/customisation;
:Submit order;

|System|
:Validate order;
:Create CustomerOrder;
:Add PrepareOrderCommand to KitchenQueue;
:Notify allergy observers if needed;

|Kitchen|
:View kitchen queue;
if (Order modified before preparing?) then (yes)
  |Waiter|
  :Modify or cancel order;
  |System|
  :Update order/audit log;
endif

|Kitchen|
:Process command;
:Set order status PREPARING;
:Prepare meal;
:Set order status SERVED;

|Cashier|
:Generate itemised bill;
:Select pricing strategy;
:Add tip and split count;

|System|
:Calculate discount, tax, split bill;
:Append record to Singleton OrderHistoryLog;
:Set table status AWAITING_BILL;

|Customer|
:Pay bill;

|Waiter|
:Clear table;

|System|
:Set table status CLEARED;
stop
@enduml
